        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I create a DB object at bootstrap by $db = Zend_Db::factory($database_config), and store it into the Registry for later use.\n\n$database_config is a Zend_Config object containing the adapter, params etc...\n\nThe problem here, is when I use a mixture of databases, say MSSQL & MYSQL.\nThe SQL statements for the two databases potentially differ.\n\nSo when writing DAOs, I need to cater for the differences. I need to know what adapter (or database type) that the $db object represents.\n\ngetDbConfig() returns params, but no adapter type.\n\nI note that there is a _pdoType in some DB Adapters, but its protected. However, this will only apply to PDO I guess.\n\nCan I request that getDbConfig() be extended to include adapter information?\nor a new function getDbAdapter().\n\n\n"
        },
